ABOUT THIS COURSE:

Welcome to Data-driven Decision Making. In this course I got an introduction to Data Analytics and its role in business decisions. I  learnt why data is important and how it has evolved. I was  introduced to “Big Data” and how it is used.I was also introduced to a framework for conducting Data Analysis and what tools and techniques are commonly used. Finally, I got a project as an opportunity to put my knowledge to work in a simulated business setting.

This course was created by PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP with an address at 300 Madison Avenue, New York, New York, 10017.


WHAT I LEARNED:

1.Introduction to Data Analytics
2.Technology and types of data
3.Data analysis techniques and tools
4.Data-driven decision making project

SKILLS DEVELOPED:

1.Data-Informed Decision-Making
2.Big Data
3.Data Analysis
4.Data Visualization (DataViz)
